======================================================================
SYNTHESIS: NUMBER-THEORETIC STRUCTURES IN H
======================================================================

1. H ≡ 0 mod p ALWAYS (for circulant tournaments)
   This follows from cyclic symmetry: Z_p acts freely on HP
   so |HP| = p · |{paths starting at 0}|

2. H/p is NOT divisible by p in general:
   p=5: H/p=5 (divisible!), p=7: H/p=25 (not), p=13: H/p=285475 (not)

3. The ratio H/mean_H is remarkably stable:
   INT: H/mean ≈ 0.68-0.71 for all p tested
   PAL: H/mean ≈ 0.73 at p=7, drops with p

4. OPEN: Is there a p-adic or class number connection?
   The Wilson quotient and class numbers don't show obvious links.
   But the STABLE H/mean ratio suggests a large-deviation principle.

